# Post types and taxonomies

Source of truth: `configure/cpt-taxonomy.php`. Flush permalinks after CPT/taxonomy/rewrite changes.

## Registering a new CPT

Use **`akademiata_register_post_type( $slug, $args )`** instead of `register_post_type()` — auto-adds `author`, `revisions`, and `akademiata_theme` flag.

## Admin history

- **Simple History** — kto / kiedy (log).
- **Autor i historia** — theme meta box (author dropdown, last save, revisions link). Native **authordiv** removed (empty on CPT). **Rewizje** meta box stays visible.

## Offer CPTs

| CPT | Archive / slug notes | Taxonomies |
|-----|----------------------|------------|
| `bachelor` | `oferta/studia-1-stopnia` | `program`, `degree`, `mode`, `obtained_title`, `promotions`, `department`, `city`, `recruitment_date`, `language`, `duration`, `post_tag` |
| `master` | `oferta/studia-2-stopnia` | same as bachelor |
| `postgraduate` | `studia-podyplomowe` | `type_of_study_pg_mba`, `duration_pg_mba`, `language_pg_mba`, `diploma_pg_mba`, `form_pg_mba`, `city_pg_mba` |
| `mba` | `studia-mba` | same PG/MBA set |

`promotions` taxonomy uses rewrite slug `promocje` (bachelor/master only).

